X: 22
T: Blessed Jesus at Thy Word
C: Words: verses 1-3, Tobias Clausnitzer, 1663. verse 4, unknown author. Translated by Catherine Winkworth, 1858.
C: Music: 'Liebster Jesu wir Sind Hier' Johann Rudolph Ahle, 1664. Setting: Fridrich Layriz, 1854.
C: SSAATTBB arr. for lever harp accompaniment. Key: G major (no transposition required).
C: copyright: public domain. Source: Open Hymnal Project, 2012 Revision.
S: Expanded from Open Hymnal SATB. Arranger: Claude Sonnet 4.6, 2026.
M: 4/4
L: 1/4
Q: 1/4=120
%%staves {(V1 V2) (V3 V4) (V5 V6) (V7 V8)}
V:1 name="Soprano I"   clef=treble
V:2 name="Soprano II"  clef=treble
V:3 name="Alto I"      clef=treble
V:4 name="Alto II"     clef=treble
V:5 name="Tenor I"     clef=treble middle=B3 transpose=-12
V:6 name="Tenor II"    clef=treble middle=B3 transpose=-12
V:7 name="Baritone"    clef=bass
V:8 name="Bass I"      clef=bass
K: G
%
% PHRASE 1 (bars 1-5): Antiphonal opening — SSAA choir only, TTBB tacet.
% Melody in S1; S2 a diatonic third below; A1 and A2 independent lines.
%
[V:1] B G A d | B G A2 | G G G G | A B A2 | G4 |
[V:2] G E F B | G E F2 | E E E E | F G F2 | E4 |
[V:3] E D D F | D C D2 | B, B, C B, | C D2 E | D4 |
[V:4] B, B, A, A, | G, A, F,2 | G, G, E, G, | A, G, F,2 | G,4 |
[V:5] z4 | z4 | z4 | z4 | z4 |
[V:6] z4 | z4 | z4 | z4 | z4 |
[V:7] z4 | z4 | z4 | z4 | z4 |
[V:8] z4 | z4 | z4 | z4 | z4 |
%
% PHRASE 2 (bars 6-10): Full 8-voice texture. TTBB enters with A phrase.
% T1 follows original tenor; T2 a diatonic third below.
% Bar harmonizes a third above B1 throughout.
%
[V:1] B G A d | B G A2 | G G G G | A B A2 | G4 |
[V:2] G E F B | G E F2 | E E E E | F G F2 | E4 |
[V:3] E D D F | D C D2 | D D E D | C D2 E | D4 |
[V:4] B, B, A, A, | B, B, A,2 | B, C E, G, | G, A, G,2 | C4 |
[V:5] G B A A | G B D2 | G B C G | C D D2 | B4 |
[V:6] E G F F | E G B,2 | E G A, E | A, B, B,2 | G,4 |
[V:7] B, B, A, F, | B, G, F,2 | D, B,, E, D, | C, B,, F,2 | D,4 |
[V:8] G, G, F, D, | G, E, D,2 | B,, G,, C, B,, | A,, G,, D,2 | G,,4 |
%
% PHRASE 3 (bars 11-15): Full 8-voice homophony. Climax at bar 14 (S1 reaches C5).
% Accidentals in original inner voices replaced diatonically (see notes).
% 4-3 suspension in A1 at penultimate bar; stretto approach at final cadence.
%
[V:1] D D E F | G A F D | !sintro!G G A B | c B A2 | G4 !eintro!|]
[V:2] B, B, C D | E F D B, | E E F G | A G F2 | E4 |]
[V:3] D E E D | D C D D | E D D B, | E D C2 | D4 |]
[V:4] C B, A, B, | C B, B, G, | A, B, A, G, | A, B, A,2 | B,4 |]
[V:5] B A G A | B A A F | G G F G | G G F2 | G4 |]
[V:6] G F E F | G F F D | E E D E | E E D2 | E4 |]
[V:7] B, A, G, G, | D, E, F, F, | D, G, F, B,, | E, B,, F,2 | B,,4 |]
[V:8] G, F, E, D, | B,, C, D, D, | B,, E, D, G,, | C, G,, D,2 | G,,4 |]
